info.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 23 at 2:00PM CST until February 24 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 9 AM CST FRIDAY... * WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as 30 below zero. * WHERE...Koochiching, North St. Louis, Northern Cook and Lake, North Itasca and Southern Cook Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Grand Portage Reservation and the Bois Forte Band, Deer Creek and, Nett Lake areas. * WHEN...From 3 AM to 9 AM CST Friday. * IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
info.instruction: Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.
